<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Inclining" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Inclining,</orth> 1) inclination, favourable disposition: <bibl n="shak. aww 3.6.41" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 6, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.283" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 283</bibl>.<lb />2) leaning, side, party chosen (cf. <cit><quote>incline:</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 42</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 3, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.6.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 6, 14</bibl>): <cit><quote>both you of my i., and the rest,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.2.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 2, 82</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>